data.title: Town of LaGrange, Indiana – Town of LaGrange, Indiana
data.text: LaGrange was platted on June 18, 1836 and began the process of becoming the County Seat by an act of the Legislature in 1840. This was an attempt to locate county seats near the center of the county population. LaGrange, meaning “farm or plantation” was named after the Marquis de Lafayette plantation. Read More
